            <abstract id="ref34" label="Abstract">The Reader’s Feast was an independent bookstore opened in 1983 in Hartford, Connecticut’s West End. The two co-managers, Carolyn Gabel and Tollie Miller, were avid women’s rights and gay rights activists and wanted to start a community bookstore where books representing all different cultures were sold and the environment was comfortable and safe for everyone. They ran the bookstore for twelve years, moving on to other ventures in 1995. This collection includes advertisements, newspaper articles, correspondence, and other materials directly related to Reader’s Feast from 1983-1996.</abstract>
            <origination label="creator">
